Package: actuaRE
Type: Package
Title: Handling hierarchically structured risk factors using random effects models
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Bavo DC Campo
Maintainer: Bavo DC Campo <bavo.decock@kuleuven.be>
Description: Using this package, you can fit a random effects model using either the hierarchical credibility model, a combination of the hierarchical credibility model with a GLM or a Tweedie generalized linear mixed model.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0), magrittr, speedglm, data.table, ggplot2, knitr, stats, methods, cplm
Imports: statmod, nlme, boot, lme4
Suggests: 
    plyr,
    insuranceData,
    actuar,
    utils
LazyData: true
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
